Michigan 74th District Court
"...The way budgets are these days, the police do not have to show up, which means they can do it from their office if they have to do anything. It eliminates the court time which means we don’t have to put that on our docket. And it also frees up time for the magistrate, of course."Hon. Thomas Truesdell 
Michigan 14A District Court
